.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-ALIAS" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-alias \- get or set the node alias
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-alias
.RI [ new-alias ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Without an argument, returns the current node alias from
.BR getinfo .
With an argument, sets the alias via
.B setconfig
(requires Core Lightning 23.11 or later).
.PP
Get output:
.nf
{"alias":"..."}
.fi
Set output:
.nf
{"ok":true,"alias":"..."}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-info (1),
.BR lightning-node-config (1)
